
### Effects

- Effects are useed to handle async operations.
-__Step 1__: Effects listen to all the actions of the app, we create a class which has the property with the decorator
__ @Effect()__ from `@ngrx/effects`.
- We can then include these effects to the imports of the module by __EffectsModule__ from `@ngrx/effects`.

```ts
import { StoreModule } from '@ngrx/store';
import { EffectsModule } from '@ngrx/effects';

@NgModule({
  declarations: [...],
  imports: [...
    StoreModule.forRoot(reducers),
    EffectsModule.forRoot([AuthEffect])
  ],
  providers: [...],
  bootstrap: [AppComponent]
})
export class AppModule { }
```
